DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$k = random(4,10,2) ;
$error = .001;
$z = $k + 1;

BEGIN_TEXT

Let \( T_{$k}(x) \) be the sixth degree Taylor polynomial of the function
\( f(x) = \ln(1+x) \) at \(a = 0 \). Suppose you approximate	\( f(x) \) by \( T_{$k}(x) \). Find all positive values of \(x\) for which this approximation
is within \($error\) of the right answer. $BR$BR

$BITALIC Hint: use the alternating series approximation. $EITALIC 

$BR$BR
\( 0 < x \leq \) \{ans_rule(15)\}

END_TEXT

$answer0 = "($error*$z)^(1/$z)";

ANS(num_cmp($answer0));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
